And how was this tree made? First this was done, then this ... You know, because it is The Tree of Knowledge.

She understands that the true spirit of the West lies in cucked multinational institutions that fawn to people like her.
You might need to take a winter vacation to Shanghai if you want to visit a Christmas Market without being massacred by Islamics. ...

... Trying to think about the cultural history of robot rebellion yesterday, but thoughts constantly interrupted by low-effort prophetic distracting whisper: "Islamist mofos are going to do a Christmas Market massacre again, aren't they?"
"C'mon, no, you're just being racist."
America is healing.
Unfortunate, if true, because that means the prophesied Islamist Christmas Market massacre is still to come.
People assure me this isn't a parody account.

An important message from The Three Sisters (Norns of the NRx Trichotomy):
1) Theonomy ("Holy Ghost has got this.")
2) Ethnonationalism ("CHIMP THE HELL OUT harder!")
3) Technocommercialism ("Let her cook.")
They're very wise.
Mine are a degenerated post-semantic version.
There should in fact be an explicit long-term project to become different species.
The entire political, bureaucratic, and judicial elite is so radically corrupt it takes statements of that kind as mitigating.
Kind of question a different species would ask.
Hyper-racism is what you're looking for (assuming it's in there).

... 
"Humanity is all in this together."
"Ewww."

On one axis there's diversity (and WEIRDs who pretend not to see it).
On another there's those ashamed of 'humanity' as a generic category, and those frantically trying to climb aboard. ...
... If the generic humanists win out, X-Risk becomes something to be extremely relaxed about.
... As a prediction: Accelerating global dysgenics is going to make generic humanism completely unsustainable other than as a psychotic death cult.

I've gone meaner before my first cup of coffee every morning than @Steve_Sailer has in his entire life. The notion he was ever cancelled says incredible things about how the Overton Window has been shifted.
... Every post I see from him I think, "Aww, what a sweet guy ... hang on, isn't he supposed to be a baddie?"
Doesn't fall off that fast in my case.

Steve's essays leave everyone thinking, "Every sane and honest person has to accept this, right?"
On mine, I cannot possibly comment.
